section.t:
The client session header is the 25 byte sequence 0x464f4f202a20485454502f322e300d0a0d0a4241520d0a0d0a (the string FOO * HTTP/2.0

BAR

) followed by a SETTINGS frame. The client sends the client session header immediately upon receipt of a 101 Switching Protocols response (indiciating a successful upgrade), or after receiving a TLS Finished message from the server. If starting HTTP/2.0 with prior knowledge, the client session header is sent upon connection establishment.
